main event: A civilian in Gales Ferry, Connecticut reported seeing an object traveling from east to west on July 25, 1965.
interesting points: The object was described as larger and longer than wide, with a wobbling motion as it descended.
The witness initially thought it was a shooting star, but the object continued moving until it disappeared on the horizon.
The witness had observed similar objects on several previous occasions over a period of several days.
The Air Force requested the witness fill out a form to report the sighting, indicating they were investigating it.
The case was not conclusively evaluated, and was left as 'insufficient data for evaluation'.
sighted object: a large, elongated object with a wobbling motion
